[{"question":"Let me start with you Brianna, what is going on down where you are and will there be any re-election tonight?","answer":"No, really at the White House, we\u0027re not expecting to see President Obama and the action very much is on the senate where allies (ph) are at the White House at this point, President Obama said today he does believe that the shutdown will be over by Thursday.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":12,"aSentId":13},{"question":"And in terms of both, which may actually lead to a real deal, what is the process?","answer":"Well, there are potential scenarios which I won\u0027t get into because it will probably make your head spin in the senate.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":25,"aSentId":26},{"question":"Is this likely?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s hard to say at this point.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":42,"aSentId":43},{"question":"What is your view of his behavior?","answer":"Well, I think that one of the things we all should do right now is not talk about personality.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":54,"aSentId":55},{"question":"At what point is the out right selfish, self-interest of Ted Cruz and his colleagues outweigh the American interest in the global economic interest?","answer":"There again, I think that we don\u0027t do is talk about personalities ...","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":73,"aSentId":74},{"question":"Are you prepared to see that risk?","answer":"Absolutely not.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":115,"aSentId":116},{"question":"... as a Party to avoid that?","answer":"I continue to work with other republicans in the House to see if we can find a resolution to this issue.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":121,"aSentId":122},{"question":"So, even if the president were in -- you know, if the president had any ability to control the republicans and the House of Representatives, which by the way, the Speaker of the House does not have as evidence by the failure of his idea today even if the president could control the House of Representatives, what would you be negotiating on?","answer":"A little later there (ph), Jim Himes and Marsha Blackburn, thank you both very much indeed.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":194,"aSentId":195},{"question":"What happens to money in America and around the world?","answer":"Nothing immediately unless there\u0027s delay in payment by the U.S. Treasury.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":212,"aSentId":213},{"question":"How does that factor rate?","answer":"Look, let me tell you the first part of that question is what happens if they don\u0027t raise the debt ceiling and the U.S. is in this case where Richard was talking about, we\u0027re trying to pick and choose which bills to pay that would be really terrible for your 401K, it would be terrible for stock.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":226,"aSentId":227},{"question":"What did you mean by that?","answer":"It\u0027s very simple Piers.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":238,"aSentId":239},{"question":"You study these markets around the world but almost anybody I know, at what point do they start to really tank (ph) and at what point does it become almost inevitable that massive financial damage will be done regardless of whether they reach any kind of law second settlement?","answer":"So, on the second issue, Piers, damage has been done, has been done to the real economy, people are spending less, companies are hiring less, so that\u0027s a real problem because it\u0027s not like our economy was growing very fast to begin with.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":255,"aSentId":256},{"question":"Is all this just going to kill that, but also we\u0027re heading back to a potential risk of recession again?","answer":"Look, it is kind of productive at best.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":283,"aSentId":284},{"question":"What is your gut feeling about how bad this is going to be?","answer":"I\u0027m worried about the complacency.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":339,"aSentId":340},{"question":"Alan Dershowitz, let me start with you because this is fascinating, do you taught Ted Cruz at Harvard?","answer":"Well I\u0027m not sure how much I taught him but I sat in the front of the class while he was in the class raising his hand, always his right hand making very intelligent points and really winning debates all the time in the class including winning debates with his professors.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":353,"aSentId":354},{"question":"One of the best students you\u0027ve had?","answer":"One of the sharpest students I had.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":355,"aSentId":356},{"question":"What do you think his strategy is?","answer":"I think he deeply believes what he\u0027s doing.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":363,"aSentId":364},{"question":"When he is basically taking an established law like ObamaCare, whether you like possibly don\u0027t know or even know a thing and using that as a stick to shut down the American government, that\u0027s taking you a bit far, isn\u0027t it principle?","answer":"Not only that I think it really raises very serious constitutional questions of the kind that Ted Cruz should be interested in.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":374,"aSentId":375},{"question":"What is the problem and from all your experience and is detailed in your book, how do we get through this?","answer":"Well, I had suggested a mediator but it\u0027s too late now we\u0027re on the brink of a major decision, a catastrophic decision that we don\u0027t take action.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":384,"aSentId":385},{"question":"Is that great leadership?","answer":"Well, if you look at the record, Piers, the president has called the leadership then (ph).","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":415,"aSentId":416},{"question":"I mean, is this split between a newly galvanized Tea Party on the main body politic of the GOP, going to be a very much of problem form (ph)?","answer":"It\u0027s going to be a problem form (ph).","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":453,"aSentId":454},{"question":"Would you like to see most members of congress reelect next election among rich (ph) voters?","answer":"No. 74 percent ...","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":466,"aSentId":467},{"question":"Did you imagine him actually making a serious run for presidency?","answer":"I think he\u0027s heard (ph) his chances of doing that because to get to be the president it\u0027s not enough to win some primaries.","docId":"131015pmt","qSentId":475,"aSentId":476}]